draw(B--O--D,dashed);
dot(A); dot(B); dot(C); dot(D); dot(EE); dot(F); dot(G); dot(H); dot(O);
[/asy] The final Answer is \frac 43
 ### Proof
 The base of the pyramid is a square of side length $2$, and thus has area $2^2=4$. The height of the pyramid is half the height of the cube, or $\frac 12\cdot 2 = 1$.
 Therefore, the volume of the pyramid is \begin{align} \frac 13\cdot (\text{area of base})\cdot (\text{height}) &= \frac 13\cdot 4\cdot 1 \\ &= \boxed{\frac 43}. \end{align}
 *)

